static boolean isAwtHeadless(org.apache.commons.logging.Log log, org.slf4j.Logger logger) {     Assert.assertFalse("Both loggers are not allowed to be null!", log == null && logger == null).     boolean headless = Boolean.getBoolean("java.awt.headless").     if (headless) {         // having the conversion characters %c{1} inside log4j.properties will reveal us the         // test class currently running as we make use of it's logger to warn about skipping!         String warning = "Running headless. Skipping test as Images may not work.".         if (log != null) {             log.warn(warning).         }         if (logger != null) {             logger.warn("Running headless.
